196
00:34:47,000 --> 00:34:58,000
One of the first things who came and sat at our table was Floyd McKissie, a young attorney.

197
00:34:58,000 --> 00:35:10,000
At that time, I knew him because he practiced taught and taught me civics at the school.

198
00:35:10,000 --> 00:35:14,000
He had applied to go to University of North Carolina and University of North Carolina.

199
00:35:14,000 --> 00:35:18,000
Built a law school rather than accepted him.

200
00:35:18,000 --> 00:35:20,000
They built a law school, right?

201
00:35:20,000 --> 00:35:25,000
Just in front of the most avenue, I'm serious.

202
00:35:25,000 --> 00:35:30,000
The first year they used the old science building.

203
00:35:30,000 --> 00:35:47,000
But by the next year, the state of North Carolina, rather than accept a black man in the law school, built an entire law program at North Carolina Central University.

204
00:35:47,000 --> 00:35:50,000
What did you think about that?

205
00:35:50,000 --> 00:35:52,000
What?

206
00:35:52,000 --> 00:36:01,000
I thought that I probably would have more people apply for different kinds of diverse programs.

207
00:36:01,000 --> 00:36:07,000
And get more programs.

208
00:36:07,000 --> 00:36:13,000
The question of integration at that time was not one of my major concerns.

209
00:36:13,000 --> 00:36:25,000
My concern was having access to something that could prepare you for life.

210
00:36:25,000 --> 00:36:28,000
So that was my attitude.

211
00:36:28,000 --> 00:36:32,000
But it was absurd.

212
00:36:32,000 --> 00:36:40,000
Everybody at my high school, hillside high school, in Durham, North Carolina, had a master's degree.

213
00:36:40,000 --> 00:36:50,000
Most of them had received it as a subsidy from the state of North Carolina.

214
00:36:50,000 --> 00:37:04,000
Rather than accept them at one of the white universities, they paid them to go to the University of Chicago to go to Columbia University.

215
00:37:04,000 --> 00:37:07,000
I mean, they actually paid them.

216
00:37:07,000 --> 00:37:14,000
So I would think about it in a different way today.

217
00:37:14,000 --> 00:37:20,000
But that was...it shows you the absurdity.

218
00:37:20,000 --> 00:37:24,000
